description.narrative:
The objective of the project is to use as a starting point the existing groups of women, empowering members of ACUMIM enhancing their capacity to participate in the development of the Island of Mozambique and to contribute to poverty eradication. 

The specific objectives of the project: 
¿ Develop the skills of entrepreneurship among women of the Association; 
¿ To provide Association of a physical office; 
¿ Literacy and educate members of ACUMIM; 
¿Develop activities that promote economic welfare, social and cultural development of members of the Association;
¿ 
The project focus directly on some 1000 people (if we consider that the average member of a household families in Mozambique is 4.8 people) which is to say that the budget availability average is 489.5 U.S. dollars per person against a value of product per capita GDP in the first semester of 2008 to U.S. $ 475.7. The rate of economic growth in recent years stands at 7%.
